('What Does a Reset Mean and How Does It Function on a Nitro X account?', '{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "A reset on a Nitro X account allows a trader who has breached their account (for example, by exceeding the Daily or Overall Loss Limit) to restore the account to its original balance at the time of purchase and start over.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Example:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "If you have a $100,000 account and breach the 3% Daily Drawdown Limit, you can reset the account via your Dashboard for a fee.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Once reset, the account returns to its initial $100,000 balance, and you can continue trading under the same rules and risk parameters.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Important Update on Resets:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 1, "version": 1}, {"type": "linebreak", "version": 1}, {"mode": "normal", "text": "Nitro X resets operates on a fixed 30-day cycle that begins on the date of your first account purchase:", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": null, "textStyle": "", "textFormat": 0}, {"type": "paragraph"